div.div:
Refactor FirebasePushController to utilize updateFCMToken method
To streamline updating the fcm_token in the FirebasePushController, the array updating method has been replaced with a call to the updateFCMToken method. This structural modification simplifies the code, enhancing readability and maintainability, while also leveraging existing methods designed specifically for these tasks.

Refactor controllers for improved code structure and efficiency
In this update, controllers have been refactored for improved code structure and efficiency. Changes include streamlining namespaces, updating the method signatures and return types, reorganizing code structure for readability, and adding rate limiting in the DeviceController. These modifications enhance code quality and functionality, making the code cleaner and more efficient.

Improve error handling for Firebase token in Push Controller
This update enhances the error handling in FirebasePushController. It checks if the FCM token is null before updating it for a user. If the token is null, an error response is returned, otherwise, the token is updated as before, providing a more robust error checking mechanism within the application.

Update status terminology for event handling
The status terminology has been updated within the event handling logic to provide clearer understanding and better workflow. The status of an old event changes from 'FINISHED' to 'ENDED' while the condition to start a new event now regards if it is not 'ENDED'.

Patch: Implement Composer Dependencies and Guidelines for Google Cloud-Core
This patch implements Composer dependencies for the Google Cloud-Core project, as well as creates a Code of Conduct and Contributing guidelines. Also including generation of test files and settings, and introducing LICENSE, SECURITY policy, and README to the project.
